OL,3,C'The job took a part of me': The
OL,4,Ctrauma of serving on the thin blue line
OL,6,F"It got to the stage you stopped
OL,7,Fcaring, you just did what you had to
OL,8,Fdo to get the call down and move off
OL,9,Fto the next one".
OL,11,F"I was a shell. I was broken. I had
OL,12,Fnightmares, I relived incidents that
OL,13,FI'd been to. It caused issues with my
OL,14,Ffamily, I was angry and I wasn't nice
OL,15,Fto be around.
OL,17,F"The job had taken a good part of me
OL,18,Faway."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/9
