OL,3,C'The job took a part of me': The
OL,4,Ctrauma of serving on the thin blue line
OL,6,FAssistant Chief Constable Bobby
OL,7,FSingleton said: ''The work of our
OL,8,Fofficers has become increasingly
OL,9,Fcomplex and importantly resource
OL,10,Fintensive.
OL,12,F"That combined with our decline in
OL,13,Fpolice numbers means our police
OL,14,Fofficers are under increasingly
OL,15,Fintolerable and unimaginable pressure
OL,16,Fand stress.
OL,18,F"A reality which is already worn out
OL,19,Fin our service delivery and that's
OL,20,Fbeen recognised in our ill health and
OL,21,Fretirement data.''
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
